
# ğŸ¥ AI-Powered Enhanced EHR Imaging & Documentation System  
An advanced Electronic Health Record (EHR) system enhanced with **Generative AI** for medical image processing, clinical documentation, and ICD-10 coding automation.  
This project was developed as part of the **Infosys Internship Program**.

---

## ğŸš€ Project Overview  
This project aims to modernize Electronic Health Records (EHR) by integrating **AI-driven medical image enhancement**, **automated clinical note generation**, and **ICD-10 coding assistance**.

Using **Generative AI (Azure OpenAI)**, the system improves patient record accuracy, reduces clinician workload, and enhances medical imaging clarity for more informed clinical decisions.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives  
- Improve medical imaging quality using GenAI  
- Automate clinical note writing  
- Auto-generate ICD-10 codes  
- Reduce manual administrative workload  
- Create a more intelligent, patient-centric EHR model  

---

## ğŸ“Œ Key Features  

### ğŸ”¹ 1. Medical Image Enhancement  
- AI-based image denoising  
- Reconstruction of MRI/CT/X-ray  
- Resolution enhancement and clearer visualization  
- Provides improved clinically interpretable images  

### ğŸ”¹ 2. Automated Clinical Documentation  
- Converts structured data into clinical notes  
- Summaries of diagnosis, history, and observations  
- Reduces 60â€“70% time spent on paperwork  

### ğŸ”¹ 3. ICD-10 Coding Automation  
- Maps symptoms/notes to ICD-10 labels  
- Smart coding suggestions  
- Reduces medical coding errors  

### ğŸ”¹ 4. Seamless EHR Integration  
- Designed to embed into hospital management workflow  
- Supports further scaling for OPD/IPD modules  

